commit.message:
Shell portability: Use the = test(1) operator instead of ==.

== is a GNU extension.

steam-api: Lower timeout to match the mobile client

This fixes random HTTP 500 responses that eventually result in
disconnects with: "Error: HTTP: Response truncated".

Revert "Makefile.am: add -no-undefined for cygwin"

This reverts commit f49e0e5222184cfd7f5452a7ea82d3b2c425b8fc.

Turns out it wasn't harmless, and it breaks mac OS. Instead of adding
platform checks here, this flag is now included in the cygwin-specific
parts of the bitlbee pkg-config file, as of bitlbee commit b9c10a1a
(version string 3.5.1+20170529+develop+18-gb9c10a1a-git)

Makefile.am: add -no-undefined for cygwin

Quoting https://cygwin.com/ml/cygwin/2013-07/msg00421.html

>despite popular misconception, this flag is harmless on non-PE targets

This also depends on changes on the bitlbee side to be able to link to
bitlbee itself, see bitlbee commit 54b2a367 (version string
3.5.1+20170513+develop+16-g54b2a367-git)

commit.message:
steam-api: set the proper client information cookies

This prevents certain requests from failing, most notably /home_process
requests.
README: added information about common issues

Added support for the new bitlbee plugin information

See bitlbee/bitlbee@d28fe1c.

Makefile: Fixed the missing steam-glib.h in the distribution tarball

This bug was introduced by f3c9f06.

Migrated to GTK-Doc

This is in preparation for the eventual migration to GObjects.
autogen: added support for the NOCONFIGURE variable

steam-api: fixed authentication failing with SteamGuard email codes

This is a regression introduced by 3a96383.
steam-api: only set the 'steamLogin' cookie with valid data
travis: only package for Coverity after success
